HEADWORD: Fossulate
<hw>Fos"su*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fossula</ets> little ditch, dim. of <ets>fossa</ets>. See
<er>Fosse</er>.]</ety> <def>Having, or surrounded by, long, narrow
depressions or furrows.</def>⟦br⟧
